# http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A potential hazard associated with a medical device, classified according to IMDRF terminology." .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#Risk> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Risk" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#RiskClass
<http://www.example.org/emdco#RiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#RiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The regulatory risk classification assigned to a medical device based on its intended purpose and associated risks." .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#RiskClass> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Risk Class" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#SafetyAlert
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#ActionType> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Communication to users regarding a safety issue." .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SafetyAlert> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Safety Alert" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#SelfTestDevice
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SelfTestDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SelfTestDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#InVitroDiagnosticDevice> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SelfTestDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An in vitro diagnostic device intended to be used by lay persons in a home environment." .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SelfTestDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Self-Test Device" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousIncident
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousIncident> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#Incident> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> _:genid2 .
_:genid2 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#minCardinality> "1"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#nonNegativeInteger> .
_:genid2 <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#onProperty> <http://www.example.org/emdco#isRelatedToRisk> .
_:genid2 <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "An incident that directly or indirectly led to death, serious deterioration of health, or a serious public health threat." .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousIncident> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Serious Incident" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousSeverity
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousSeverity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousSeverity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#SeverityLevel> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousSeverity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Risk event that causes serious but potentially reversible harm." .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeriousSeverity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Serious Severity" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#SeverityLevel
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeverityLevel> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeverityLevel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The degree of harm or impact associated with a risk event." .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SeverityLevel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Severity Level" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#SingleUseDevice
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SingleUseDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SingleUseDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#MedicalDevice> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SingleUseDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A device intended to be used on one individual during a single procedure." .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#SingleUseDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Single-Use Device" .
# 
# http://www.example.org/emdco#UserNotice
<http://www.example.org/emdco#UserNotice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#UserNotice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.example.org/emdco#ActionType> .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#UserNotice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Notice to users with instructions to avoid or mitigate risk." .
<http://www.example.org/emdco#UserNotice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "User Notice" .
